Germany’s Asmussen Sees Monetary System Progress, Reuters Says

-- B y   H o l g e r   E l f e s
-- 
2011-04-14T19:59:14Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-14/germany-s-asmussen-sees-monetary-system-progress-reuters-says.html
German Deputy Finance Minister
Joerg Asmussen said “good progress” has been made on plans to
reform the global monetary system,  Reuters  reported today,
citing an interview.  Asmussen, co-leader of a task force preparing the next G-20
summit, said agreement is possible on control of capital flows
and the enlargement of the special drawing rights basket,
Reuters said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Holger Elfes in Dusseldorf at 
